                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13813807" author="slebresne" created="Tue, 5 Nov 2013 09:40:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is a typo in the serialization of PagedRangeCommand so that if it has index expressions, it serializes their value with a 4-bytes length but read them with short 2-bytes length. In practice, this ends up breaking the underlying connection and results in query timeouts as described in &lt;a href=&quot;https://groups.google.com/a/lists.datastax.com/d/msg/java-driver-user/ao1ohSLpjRM/4rfCNk1OUM0J&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;this thread&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch attached. The patch also fixes a few problem in the serializedSize() method (though I don&apos;t think it&apos;s used in practice).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13813907" author="iamaleksey" created="Tue, 5 Nov 2013 13:13:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13813993" author="slebresne" created="Tue, 5 Nov 2013 15:35:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
